---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const page = {
  title: "Mulching Services | Edwards Landscape Group",
  description: "Refresh your beds with premium mulching from Edwards Landscape Group. We install clean edges, the right mulch depth, and professional finishes for healthier soil and standout curb appeal.",
  keywords: "mulching lynchburg, mulch installation, bed edging, landscape mulch"
};
---

<BaseLayout {...page}>
<main>
      <section class="service-hero service-hero--trugreen" style="background-image: url('images/Mulching_service.jpg');">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-6 hero-content-block">
              <div class="hero-kicker">Mulching</div>
              <h1 class="mb-3">Color, moisture control, and crisp beds in one visit</h1>
              <p class="mb-4 lead">Slim TruGreen-inspired banner with left-anchored copy—no yellow accents, just clear reasons to refresh your beds.</p>
              <div class="hero-meta mb-4">
                <span class="tg-badge">Dyed &amp; natural options</span>
                <span class="tg-badge">Bed prep included</span>
                <span class="tg-badge">Sharp, slim edging</span>
              </div>
              <div class="hero-actions d-flex flex-wrap">
                <a href="contact.html" class="btn btn-primary mr-2 mb-2">Schedule mulching</a>
                <a href="services.html" class="btn btn-outline-light mb-2">See all services</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section bg-light">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">Mulch palette</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Pick a finish that fits your landscape</h2>
          <div class="style-swatches">
            <div class="swatch">Espresso brown</div>
            <div class="swatch">Classic black</div>
            <div class="swatch">Warm cedar</div>
            <div class="swatch">Natural hardwood</div>
            <div class="swatch">Playground-safe chips</div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 mb-0">We source consistent color lots and install at the right depth to protect soil temperature and moisture.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">Install approach</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Prep, edge, and place for lasting color</h2>
          <div class="row gutter-40 align-items-start">
            <div class="col-lg-5">
              <div class="tg-card h-100">
                <h3>Bed prep</h3>
                <ul class="checklist">
                  <li>Remove weeds and debris, loosen crusted soil for better water exchange.</li>
                  <li>Cut a slim trench edge that keeps mulch off turf and hardscape.</li>
                  <li>Feather high spots and smooth around shrubs for a finished grade.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-7">
              <div class="tg-card highlight-card h-100">
                <h3>Placement options</h3>
                <div class="two-col-list">
                  <div>
                    <h5>Refresh</h5>
                    <p>Top off existing mulch with a color-matched layer for a quick lift.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h5>Full reset</h5>
                    <p>Strip faded product, reshape beds, and install a fresh base at proper depth.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h5>Play &amp; pet friendly</h5>
                    <p>Install chips where kids and pets roam, with edging that keeps material contained.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <a href="contact.html" class="btn btn-primary mt-3">Build my mulch plan</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section bg-light">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">Schedule map</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Plan installs around weather and color goals</h2>
          <div class="row gutter-40 align-items-start">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
              <div class="timeline-rail">
                <div class="rail-item">
                  <span class="rail-dot"></span>
                  <h4>Early spring</h4>
                  <p>Book March–April to lock in the freshest color lots and prep beds before weeds surface.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rail-item">
                  <span class="rail-dot"></span>
                  <h4>Summer refresh</h4>
                  <p>Add a light top-off in July for shaded beds to keep tones rich through heat.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rail-item">
                  <span class="rail-dot"></span>
                  <h4>Fall lock</h4>
                  <p>Install in October to insulate roots, reduce frost heave, and keep storm washouts in check.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
              <div class="service-accordion">
                <details open>
                  <summary>Can I mix colors between beds?</summary>
                  <p>Yes—front beds often get espresso while natural hardwood softens backyard plantings. We’ll edge between for a clean break.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                  <summary>How do you keep mulch off hard surfaces?</summary>
                  <p>We trench a slim edge, tarp hardscape, and finish with a blower sweep so stones and walkways stay spotless.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                  <summary>What about rain on install day?</summary>
                  <p>Light rain is fine and even helps color set. Heavy rain reschedules automatically—no extra fee.</p>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section bg-light">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">Seasonal payoffs</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">How fresh mulch works through the year</h2>
          <div class="service-timeline">
            <div class="timeline-step">
              <div class="timeline-dot">Spring</div>
              <div>
                <h4>Jump-start growth</h4>
                <p>Locks moisture for new plantings and suppresses weeds before they sprout.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-step">
              <div class="timeline-dot">Summer</div>
              <div>
                <h4>Heat protection</h4>
                <p>Shields roots from harsh temps and keeps soil from baking near foundations.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-step">
              <div class="timeline-dot">Fall</div>
              <div>
                <h4>Storm-ready</h4>
                <p>Holds soil in place and prevents washouts as storms roll through.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">Care tips</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Keep beds tidy between visits</h2>
          <div class="tg-card-grid three-col">
            <div class="tg-card">
              <h3>Quick fluff</h3>
              <p>Rake lightly once a month to keep color bright and avoid matting.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tg-card">
              <h3>Water check</h3>
              <p>After installs, water beds to settle fibers and lock coverage in place.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tg-card">
              <h3>Bundle it</h3>
              <p>Pair mulching with bed maintenance for weed pulls and shrub shaping on each visit.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
